So sit back and enjoy getting naked with me :P
P.S. All of these products are available now on their website!

This time tomorrow our newest @moana_bikini collection is going LIVE!

This has been one of my FAVOURITE campaigns I’ve ever planned and executed!

The video, music, babes and vibes really do say it all.

I’m SO incredibly proud of MOANA and what it represents for ALL women.

I can humbly say that NO other swim label on the planet is on our level. And they never will be🤭

We care SO much for each and every girl in our Moana Army and spend so much time learning, listening and talking to them. It’s something that no other brand does.

I love you all SO puppy much, words can not describe.

Please enjoy our new campaign video and dance along with us

👇🏽
Ok so I did a pole asking if you wanted this video and 96% of you said YES!

Now I’m not taking a stab at fitness influencers by any means!

I understand they need to show their audience perfect form, and easy to understand angles, and I’m all for that!

But I also know that 99% of us girls see these amazing fit females online and compare why our look, form and bodies don’t look like theirs while performing the same exercises.

It’s important to remember that most fitness influencers train hard and consistently as their full time job.
Fitness is their passion and they dedicate a lot of time into their work. 
So for people like us, who enjoy working out but it’s also not our full time job or passion we will always look different.

And that’s fine!

So here are some normal angles of my body working out as if I where looking into a mirror and seeing myself.

No editing. No colour grading. Just real life.

Never comparing yourself to another❤️

I know that this year has been rocky and many of us are feeling it.

Remembering these moments warm my heart and makes me eager to invite you all to another meetup as soon as we can to get all the good vibes and positive energy flowing!

And with that being said I do want to address an extremely commonly asked question I’ve been receiving lately. When will our next Moana Army Meetup be?

We had actually planned a meetup in Newcastle Australia for last week! However due to COVID unfortunately we had to cancel those events.

So with that being said I wanted to throw it back to YOU!

WHERE ARE YOU?

We are in process of planning one domestic and one international (once travel is allowed of course) meet up! 
Remember you don’t need to own or even wear a bikini to be apart of our meetups! We’d just love you there to meet other like minded women. Have fun. Dance. Connect. And of course, feel like the amazing boss Queen that you truly are!

I swear there is magic at our meetups and I know everyone who comes down feels it too.

Everyone is welcome❤️

I can’t believe I spent so much of my teenage years and early 20s striving to have zero rolls and creases on my tummy 🤦🏼‍♀️ 

I don’t know if it’s because of all the gossip magazines or the size 0 actresses #only starting in films and TV at the time. But it was something I was quite obsessed with wanting.

I look back on that time and think - “Wow how exhausting!”

It is such a relief to finally except my body for what it is, that being a fine working machine that is keeping me alive 🥳🤩

Tummy rolls don’t make you fat, ugly or unhealthy. 

You might not look like the character Marissa from the OC, but let’s face it… not many people do.

LET DOWN YOUR GOD DAMN HAIR🥳

The world is such a tense and opinionated place. Especially lately.

My profile and presents online is all about having some fun and not taking everything so seriously.

So please… put all your anger, frustration and briefs aside for 3 min & 22 sec and shake it out to this cheeses classic - Steps - 5,6,7,8.

It will get your endorphins pumping and help you loosen up.

Dance like no one is watching… unless you’re like me and enjoy posting it on the internet 🤣😝🤪

DELETED FILES… 🗝🔓

Having a #BLOATED AF day, and thought it would irresponsible to not share and only post a posed photo.

I’m currently half way through my girlie cycle and this is normally where I bloat the most🩸 🤰🏼

Please DON’T tell me I’m fat.
Please DON’T tell me I should be gluten free.
Please DON’T tell me I need to be vegan.
Please DON’T tell me I need to workout.

This is just being a woman, and if you don’t understand that, then run along 💁‍♀️

I love sharing my bloated photos and videos but don’t appreciate unqualified Instagram doctors trying to explain WHY I’m bloated and instilling fear into myself and others🙅‍♀️

No one knows your body better than you do. Listen to it. Not strangers opinions on it.

Just accept that every body bloats from time to time. And it’s something that needs to be normalised more.

There’s nothing wrong with you. You might just need to fart…😆 💨

node.text:
LOCKDOWN VIBES 🔐 

Currently on the Gold Coast in Australia we are on a mini COVID lockdown… 

And I say mini because (so far) it’s just a week. 

I’m so disappointed to see people out and about with friends, protesting, socialising and just generally choosing to disregard public health advice.

We have been pretty lucky here in Australia when it comes to COVID, and this comes down to our prompt and strict lockdowns while we wait for vaccines to become available. The absolute LEAST we can do is STAY HOME. It’s not really that hard. It’s one week. 

With only three days left of lockdown and our local numbers still increasing, try to understand the difference between inconvenience and injustice. What you’re going through isn’t really that bad, compared to the alternative.
